<TEXT>
   The Associated Press erroneously reported
Wednesday that Procter & Gamble Co. contributed 56,000 books of
baseball cards, valued at $500,000 or more, to a fund aimed at
helping destitute former players.
   The contribution of Surf Baseball Card Collectibles to the
