<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF-Soldier Earring,0128</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Court Rules Soldiers Can Wear Earring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Male Norwegian soldiers can wear an earring
if they wish, a court has ruled.
   The civilian court in Hammerfest, Norway's northernmost town,
recently handed down the decision on a soldier's appeal against a
$48 fine he received last fall for refusing to remove a small
earring, the national NTB news agency reported.
   NTB quoted the Finnmark Dagblad newspaper, published in Tromsoe,
as saying the unidentified soldier challenged a military regulation
stating that only women are allowed to wear ``ear jewelry.''
   The magistrates voted 2-1 that the code was discriminatory. The
two judges voting in the soldier's favor were women, while the male
judge voted to uphold the previous dress codes, NTB reported.
</TEXT>
