<1ST_LINE>r a PM-DancersCovered     06-02 0245</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Dancers Covered,0252</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>City Covers Up Pornography Law's Loophole</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents</NOTE>
<DATELINE>EL PASO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Flustered City Council members closed a
loophole in a pornography ordinance after topless dancers began
smearing themselves with transparent grease to slip out of a
requirement that they cover up.
   Before it was amended Tuesday, the ordinance specified what
parts of dancers' bodies had to be covered but didn't say the
covering had to be opaque.
   ``Some of the girls ... were covering their breasts with
Vaseline or grease,'' said Brenda Nichols, assistant city attorney.
   There were reports that other dancers used see-through fabric
and clear adhesive tape to skirt the ordinance. Tuesday's Council
action banned all such clear coverings.
   The Council also amended the ordinance to make sure adult
entertainment establishments are at least 1,000 feet from homes,
schools, churches, parks or other adult businesses.
   The amendment went into effect immediately.
   Those who still want to see strippers can easily cross an
international bridge to Ciudad Juarez, Mexico, where nude dancing
and prostitution are legal.
   Mike Gibson, a lawyer who represents some of the adult
businesses here, said City Council simply is trying to stamp out
adult businesses in El Paso.
   ``If you comply with the first ordinance they pass, they change
it to make sure no one can comply,'' he said. ``With the new
definition of the type of covering, you might as well set up
outside a swimming pool and charge admission to it.''
</TEXT>
