<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Academy Family,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Family Chalks Up 7th Air Acacemy Graduate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Second Lt. John Cartwright
Vanderburgh has become the seventh member of his family to graduate
from the U.S. Air Force Academy.
   Four older brothers and two sisters graduated from the academy
and remain active in the Air Force. A fifth brother graduated from
West Point.
   ``It's a very happy day,'' the 21-year-old Vanderburgh said
Wednesday. ``Everybody's really excited.''
   Vanderburgh's father, Richard, was an Air Force fighter pilot
captain in the Korean War. He and his wife, Mary, who attended
Wednesday's graduation, hold civilian jobs at Wright Patterson AFB
in Dayton, Ohio.
   Vanderburgh's younger brother Robert is attending the University
of Dayton, where he is in the Air Force ROTC program. Another
younger brother, Michael, is a high school junior but plans to go
into law enforcement.
   Academy officials did not know immediately whether the family
set a record for the most siblings to graduate.
</TEXT>
