<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Argentina-Cold     06-02 0193</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Argentina-Cold,0200</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Death Toll From Cold Wave Hits 11 In Argentina</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALTA, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A cold spell that sent temperatures
plunging to 3 degrees in southern Patagonia has led to the deaths
of at least 11 people, authorities say.
   Winter is still 20 days away in the Southern Hemisphere, but the
cold snap has forced pedestrians in Buenos Aires to don ski parkas
and hand mittens.
   And heavy snows have already closed several passes in the Andes
mountains between Chile and Argentina.
   On Wednesday, police discovered the 11th victim, a man frozen to
death in this northwestern city.
   In other incidents, authorities said three brothers burned to
death in southwestern Neuquen Province when their stove overheated
and caught fire, two men were found frozen to death in northwestern
Cordoba Province and a middle-aged couple died of asphyxiation when
their heating system failed in Buenos Aires Province.
   On Tuesday, authorities found the bodies of a baby girl and an
elderly man from the resort of Mar del Plata and another man near
downtown Salta.
   Mar del Plata is 250 miles south of Buenos Aires. Salta is 1,000
miles northwest of the capital.
</TEXT>
