<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Japan-Markets 2ndLd-Writethru a0401 06-02 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets, 2nd Ld-Writethru, a0401,0164</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar, Stock Prices Advance</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES with closing market figures.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices rose across the board Thursday on the
Tokyo Stock Exchange while the dollar also scored a sharp gain
against the Japanese yen.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, the exchange's
main barometer, gained 165.45 points to close at 27,869.36, 0.59
percent higher than Wednesday's close.
   The dollar also rose 0.33 yen to end the day's trading at 125.68
yen.
   ``The situation in New York is encouraging investors,'' said a
broker at a major securities firm who requested anonymity. ``But
investors' concern over inflation and rising interest rates also
remains strong, and it is keeping share prices from skyrocketing.''
   Earlier in the day the index soared to 27,930.58 points, but
profit-taking by investors brought the index back down, traders
said.
   Volume on the first section was 1.3 billion shares. Securities
and marine transports were being sought, while banks were weak.
</TEXT>
