<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     06-02 0403</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0416</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Generate High Wind, Rain</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms rumbled over many sections of the nation early
today after dumping heavy rain on Baton Rouge, La., and whipping up
high winds in New Jersey.
   Gusts neared 60 mph at Hamilton Square, N.J., on Wednesday
evening, while a small cluster of thunderstorms over Baton Rouge
produced an inch of rain in less than an hour.
   Showers and thunderstorms continued into the morning along the
Oregon coast; in the northern Rockies; from northwest Texas to
Oklahoma and southeast Kansas; in southeast Louisiana and southwest
Mississippi; from Iowa to Nebraska, South Dakota, southeastern
North Dakota and western Minnesota; and from lower Michigan to
northeast Ohio, Pennsylvania, northern Virginia, Maryland, New
Jersey and southeast New England.
   Heavier rainfall during the 6 hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT
included 2 inches at Baton Rouge, an inch and a half at
Wrightstown, N.J., and more than an inch at Homestead, Fla.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms over the
   middle Mississippi Valley, showers across northern New England
and rain over the Pacific Northwest.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 50s and 60s in New
England; the 60s in the Great Lakes region, from the northern
Appalachians to New Jersey, and in the Pacific Northwest; the 90s
from Mississippi to Georgia and North Carolina, and in central and
western Texas; and the 90s to 110 degrees in the desert Southwest.
Elsewhere, highs in the 70s and 80s were predicted.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 35 at
Watertown, N.Y., to 82 at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 72 fair; Boston 54 windy; Buffalo 45 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 72 fair; Cincinnati 63 fair; Cleveland 53
showers; Detroit 54 cloudy; Miami 76 showers; New York 57 windy;
Philadelphia 59 cloudy; Pittsburgh 55 showers; Portland, Maine, 46
partly cloudy; Washington 71 windy.
   _Central: Bismarck 67 cloudy; Chicago 78 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 71 fair; Denver 60 fair; Des Moines 65 rain;
Indianapolis 70 hazy; Kansas City 63 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 73
partly cloudy; Nashville 65 hazy; New Orleans 72 fair; St. Louis 71
hazy.
   _West: Albuquerque 66 partly cloudy; Anchorage 52 cloudy; Las
Vegas 72 fair; Los Angeles 61 fair; Phoenix 82 partly cloudy; Salt
Lake City 56 partly cloudy; San Diego 63 fair; San Francisco 57
partly cloudy; Seattle 49 partly cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 43 fair; Toronto 45 fair.
