<2ND_LINE>PM-Molest Suspect,0266</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suspect Claims To Have Molested 300 Children</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COMMERCE CITY, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man arrested on charges of
sexually assaulting a 3-year-old claims to have molested 200 to 300
children in the past 20 years, police said.
   Law enforcement agencies in the Denver metropolitan area are
investigating the claims made by Rodney O. Bailey, 44, police in
this Denver suburb said.
   Bailey was arrested May 19 on charges of sexually assaulting a
girl in a vehicle in his garage April 12 after the child wandered
into the yard where he and his wife were working, police said. He
was freed on $5,000 bail.
   In a statement to police, Bailey, a machine operator for a
bottling company, said he molested 3- to 8-year-old boys and girls
throughout the metropolitan area, mostly in toy departments of
large stores, police said.
   ``He would look for a child left alone, approach them, strike up
a conversation and then fondle them,'' said Detective Jan Brace.
``He estimated between 200 and 300. ... There could be more. That
was strictly an estimate.''
   Police said they believe many of the cases in which Bailey
claims to have been involved never were reported.
   ``It is not unusual that small children wouldn't have told
anyone about these incidents because of fear,'' Brace said.
   Bailey had two previous arrests. In 1979 he pleaded guilty to
sexually assaulting a woman, and in 1981 he was accused of
harassing a 4-year-old girl, records showed. The outcome of that
case could not immediately be determined.
</TEXT>
