<HEAD>Filming Begins for Joe Clark Movie at Eastside High</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PATERSON, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tough-guy principal Joe Clark says six
weeks of filming under way at Eastside High School may produce a
good movie but will never capture his personality.
   ``He's a good actor but I don't think anybody can fully portray
me,'' Clark said of actor Morgan Freeman on Wednesday, the first
day of filming at the inner-city school. ``There's only one Joe
Clark.''
   Clark gained national prominence and praise from the Reagan
administration by roaming the halls of Eastside with a baseball bat
and bullhorn.
   Warner Brothers decided to film his life story, ``Lean on Me''
at Eastside. Clark stands to gain a small percentage of the film's
$10 million cost, but the exact amount was not released.
   Clark called the movie ``a vindication of what I stand for'' and
said his students were holding their ``heads high, their chests are
out and joy bells are ringing in their souls.''
