<2ND_LINE>PM-Stroller Repair,150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Perego to Repair Strollers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The distributer of ``Avanti'' strollers, sold
nationwide, is offering a kit to repair a design problem that has
resulted in cuts and other injuries to children, the Consumer
Product Safety Commission said today.
   The commission said 13 instances have been reported in which
children have had their chin caught between a metal wire guide and
the arm rest, leading to mouth cuts and damaged teeth.
   Involved are ``Avanti'' strollers sold nationally by Peg Perego
U.S.A., Inc., based in Fort Wayne, Ind. The commission said 11,344
of the strollers were sold for $99 each in 1986.
   The company will provide a repair kit to close the gap between
the arm rest and guide wire. To obtain the kit and installation
instructions, consumers can call Peg Perego at 1-800-824-4000 or
write to the company at 3625 Independence Drive, Fort Wayne, Ind.
   Persons needing more information can call the commission at
1-800-638-2772.
