<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Tower Collapse,0105</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>TV Tower Collapses, At Least One Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLONY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 2,000-foot TV tower collapsed today,
killing at least one workman and leaving two others missing in the
wreckage, authorities said.
   ``We do have one fatality and possibly more,'' said Sgt. Ron
Lenzini of the Missouri State Highway Patrol at Macon. ``We really
don't know what happened.''
   The tower belonged to KTVO in Kirksville, which went on the air
in September, said Kurt Sweeney, station news director.
   The men were doing maintenance work at about 500 feet when the
tower collapsed about 10 a.m., authorities said.
</TEXT>
