<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Bank Fishing,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Charged With Using Fishing Equipment To Steal From Deposit
Slot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PENDLETON, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man used fishing equipment to reel in
two bags of money from a bank night-deposit slot, police said.
   Edwin R. Everett, 31, was charged with burglary and possession
of methamphetamine and was being held Wednesday on $15,000 bail.
   Everett used a fishing line, hook and sinker tied to a tree
branch to try to lift money from two banks Monday and Tuesday,
Police Chief Ed Taber said.
   Two bags containing $504 in cash and $979 in checks were stolen
from one bank, Taber said. The fishing line and hook snagged in the
other bank's slot, and no money was taken, the chief added. The
stolen money was not recovered.
</TEXT>
