<HEAD>Idaho Man Arrested In Kidnapping and Abuse of Child</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRIGHAM CITY, Utah (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Utah man has been charged in the
kidnapping and sexual assault of a 6-year-old girl more than a year
ago, and a judge has dismissed charges against a man who had been
convicted of the crimes.
   Thomas C. Headley, 31, of Snowville, was arrested Wednesday and
was being held in the Box Elder County Jail in lieu of $75,000 bail.
   He was to be arraigned Thursday on one count each of aggravated
sexual abuse of a child, child kidnapping and aggravated
kidnapping, all first-degree felonies, said a secretary to Box
Elder County Attorney Jon Bunderson.
   Frank James Harvey, 45, Elma, Wash., was convicted of kidnapping
and sexually assaulting the child and was sentenced to 16 years in
prison, but was released on his own recognizance in January,
pending a new trial after authorities said they had uncovered a new
suspect.
   First District Judge Gordon Low on Wednesday dismissed charges
against Harvey, the judge's clerk said.
   The girl was kidnapped March 24, 1987, from outside a school and
was released the following morning in Malta, Idaho, about 65 miles
away. She told police she had been abducted by a man driving a
four-door blue car with a dachshund in it.
   Harvey was arrested at a rest stop on Interstate 15 near
Corrine. He was driving a four-door blue car with a dachshund in
the back.
   During the trial last August, the girl could not identify Harvey
as her abductor.
   Harvey had contended he was at the Juniper, Idaho, rest stop at
the time of the abduction, and an attendant testified he remembered
seeing a man resembling Harvey shaving at the rest stop at that
time.
   The child picked Headley out of a recent photo lineup, according
to a probable cause statement accompanying the charges.
