<HEAD>One Slain, Two Wounded In Shooting Rampage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A school bus driver was slain in
front of his 8-year-old son aboard the bus today by a gunman who
then went to a retirement home and shot his former girlfriend and
himself, police and witnesses said.
   The gunman and the woman, an employee at Olds Manor Retirement
Residence, were in critical condition today at Butterworth
Hospital, said spokeswoman Patty Eddington.
   The bus driver had tried to date the retirement home employee,
Sylvia DeLeon, 23, who had recently broken off a relationship with
the gunman, according to relatives.
   The gunman, Jose Gonzalez, 34, had boaded the bus outside his
apartment and fired at bus driver Juan Vargas, 34, three times,
said police Lt. Victor Gillis. Vargas' son, Jose, was the only
child aboard, police said.
   Gonzalez had argued with Vargas about Vargas' relationship with
DeLeon on Wednesday night, said the gunman's sister-in-law, Evelyn
Gonzalez, who lives in an apartment downstairs from Gonzalez.
   Just before the shooting on the bus, Gonzalez gave his
sister-in-law an envelope in which he had written instructions in
case something happened, Mrs. Gonzalez said.
   ``He came down here, gave me a hug and a kiss and said, `I love
you,''' Mrs. Gonzalez said. She said he walked out of the house as
the bus approached. ``When I saw the (bus) coming, I hurried up and
got my husband, but it was too late,'' she said.
   After the first shooting, the gunman drove his car to Olds Manor
and shot DeLeon in a dining room, Gillis said. The gunman then ran
to another room, where he was confronted by police and shot himself
in the head, Gillis said.
   Helen Jackson, housekeeper who was in a room adjacent to where
DeLeon was wounded, said she heard a woman screaming, ``Help me,
help me'' before the shots were fired.
</TEXT>
