<HEAD>Bob Hope Wants To Pitch In Mandrell Classic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bob Hope's hands may be more accustomed
to a golf club than a bat, but the comedian is warming up to be a
team captain in the Barbara Mandrell Celebrity Softball Classic.
   By the end of the year, the 85-year-old comic will have made
about 80 charity appearances, including Mandrell's annual outing,
which takes place Friday.
   ``This one was an easy decision. Barbara called and asked, and I
said yes,'' he said from his home in Taluca Lake, Calif. ``But I
told her that if I couldn't pitch, I wouldn't play. I told her I'd
