<1ST_LINE>r i AM-HitlerBunker     06-02 0191</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Hitler Bunker,0195</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>East Germans Destroy, Clear Remains of Hitler Bunker</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The remains of the bunker where Adolf Hitler
committed suicide were destroyed to make room for a housing project
in East Berlin, the state-run East German news agency reported
Thursday.
   ``For the new building project, the former bunker site was
cleared over the past few months with numerous blastings and with
wreckage collection teams,'' the ADN news agency report said.
   During World War II, Hitler and other Nazi officials often used
bunker complexes in Berlin, then the capital of Germany, to direct
the war and seek protection for Allied bomb attacks.
   To avoid capture when the war ended, Hitler and his companion
Eva Braun killed themselves in the chancellory bunker, which was on
what now is part of the construction site in East Berlin.
   In recent years, the site next to the Berlin Wall was only a
pile of rubble that had become overgrown with grass and weeds.
   ADN said apartments for about 3,000 people will be constructed
there. It said a shopping center, school and kindergarten also will
be constructed as part of the project.
</TEXT>
