<FILEID>AP-NR-06-02-88 0824EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u f PM-Fleming-Malone     06-02 0348</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Fleming-Malone,0361</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fleming Plans to Acquire Memphis Wholesaler</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fleming Companies Inc. of Oklahoma City
will become the nation's largest food wholesaler _ supplying 5,700
retailers in 37 states _ with the acquisition of a rival
Memphis-based company, Fleming announced.
   Fleming announced Wednesday it will pay $225 million in cash to
acquire all of the outstanding stock of Malone & Hyde Inc. The
Memphis wholesaler, now the country's fourth largest, projects
sales of $3 billion for 1988.
   With 1987 sales of $8.6 billion, Fleming ranked second only to
the Super Valu grocery operation in Minneapolis. Fleming's sales
will surpass Super Valu's after the Malone & Hyde acquisition, said
James W. Clark, a Fleming vice president.
   Malone & Hyde will become a subsidiary of Fleming, Clark said.
In addition to the cash payment, Fleming will assume $375 million
of the acquired company's debt. Fleming said it expects to finance
the acquisition through sale of stock and long-term debt.
   Malone & Hyde operates eight distribution centers that supply
1,750 retail grocers in 16 states, primarily independent stores in
the Southeast. Clark said Malone & Hyde owns a few of the stores it
supplies as well as 101 retail drug stores.
   The core of Fleming's business is supplying independent grocers.
   The firms said the agreement has been approved by both companies
and is now subject to regulatory approval. The deal is expected to
close by Aug. 1.
   Malone & Hyde operates 3.3 million square feet of distribution
space at locations in Southhaven, Miss.; Goodlettsville, Tenn.;
Miami; Monroe and Layfayette, La.; Sikeston, Mo.; Nicholasville,
Ky.; and Tupelo, Miss. The company also operates a general
merchandise distribution center in Memphis and dairy plants in
Nashville, Tenn., and Baton Rouge, La.
   The company employs 9,000 people.
   Malone & Hyde was founded in 1907 and became a publicly owned
company with a stock offering in 1961. It was listed on the New
York Stock Exchange beginning in 1971.
   In 1984, the firm returned to private ownership through a buyout
led by management and the investment firm Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &
Co.
</TEXT>
