<HEAD>Conference Postponed Due to Arab Summit</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New throughout with OPEC confirmation. PRECEDES London.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Organization of the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries has postponed next week's meeting by
three days, probably due to an Arab summit meeting in Algeria, an
OPEC spokesman said today.
   He confirmed reports that the oil ministers from OPEC's 13
member nations would start their conference on June 11 rather than
Wednesday as had been planned.
   ``There is no official reason for the postponement, but most
likely the meeting was dealyed because it coincided with the Arab
summit meeting in Algiers'' that starts Tuesday, the spokesman said.
</TEXT>
