<HEAD>London Share Prices Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices on the London Stock Exchange rose
slightly Thursday late in the day after Wall Street erased some of
its earlier losses.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
stood at 1,810.3, up 4.6 points or .33 percent.
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average, off as much as 18 points at
the New York opening, recovered slightly by the close of trading
here.
   Analysts said there was a dearth of news in the market to
influence trading.
   ``There's just nothing to get excited about in this market,''
said Anthony Abrahams, Managing Director of U.K. Equity Trading at
Smith New Court Ltd. in London, adding that ``there's only marginal
movement'' in share prices.
   Only selected equities were affected after the Bank of England
signaled a half-point rise in base rates to 8.0 percent from 7 1@2
percent around midday. Major banks followed the central bank's lead
by announcing they would raise their base lending rates 0.5
percentage point to 8.0 percent, effective Friday. The interest
rate hike was not enough to lift the sinking pound.
</TEXT>
