<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. dollar scored a sharp gain against the
Japanese yen Friday, while stock prices rose slightly for the fifth
consecutive day on the Tokyo Stock Exchange.
   In response to a sharp gain overnight in New York and London,
the dollar opened at 126.07 yen, 0.39 yen higher than Thursday's
close. The upward trend carried through the morning, and the U.S.
unit was changing hands at 126.20 yen at 11:30 a.m. local time.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, the market's main index, gained 9.35 points, or
0.03 percent, to finish the morning session at 27,878.71 points.
   Volume on the first section was a moderate 800 million shares.
